{
  "texts": [
    "Additionally, ensuring the generalizability of CSL techniques across different medical datasets and settings is crucial for their practical application and broader adoption in the field.",
    "Considering the interpretability of CSL models is also essential for fostering trust and transparency in medical decision-making processes.",
    "Furthermore, promoting reproducibility by sharing datasets, code, and detailed reporting of CSL approaches enhances collaboration and facilitates comparisons between different methods.",
    "Lastly, there is a need for further exploration and application of CSL techniques on multilabel and regression problems.",
    "Such efforts hold great potential for advancing accurate and cost-aware modelling in various imbalanced contexts."
  ]
}